>> title: Hearty Vegan Chili
>> cuisine: American
>> tags: protein, vegan, gluten-free, soy-free
>> servings: 10
>> yield: 10 cups
>> storage_days: 5
>> storage_method: refrigerated
>> freezer_days: 90
>> reheat: Microwave or stovetop until heated through.

Heat @olive oil{2%tbsp} in #large pot{} or #instant pot{} over medium-high heat.

Add @yellow onion{1%large}(diced) and @bell pepper{1}(diced). Cook, stirring occasionally, ~{5%minutes} until softened.

Add @garlic{4%cloves}(minced) and @jalapenos{2-3}(seeded and minced). Cook ~{1%minute}.

Add @chili powder{2%tbsp}, @ground cumin{1%tbsp}, @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, @ground coriander{1%tsp}, @cinnamon{1/2%tsp}, and @cayenne{1/4%tsp}(more for heat). Stir to coat, cook ~{1%minute}.

Add @crushed tomatoes{1%can}(28 oz), @fire-roasted diced tomatoes{1%can}(14 oz), @tomato paste{2%tbsp}, @black beans{2%cans}(15 oz each, drained and rinsed), @kidney beans{2%cans}(15 oz each, drained and rinsed), @vegetable broth{1%cup}, @kosher salt{1%tsp}, @bay leaves{2}, and @maple syrup{1%tbsp}.

== Instant Pot Method

Pressure cook ~{15%minutes}, natural release.

== Stovetop Method

Bring to boil, reduce heat, and simmer ~{45-60%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

== Finishing

Remove bay leaves. Stir in @fresh lime juice{2%tbsp}.

Taste and adjust seasoning.

Let cool and store in #airtight containers{}.

-- Serving: Top with diced avocado, vegan sour cream, cilantro, green onions. Serve with cornbread.
